If the bounding box of the graphic node is null, which can happend to a 
composite graphic node when it lost all children, then intersects throws a 
NullPointerException because it does not check if the bounding box is valid 
first.

Here is the code for it from :
org.apache.batik.gvt.AbstractGraphicsNode : line 878

    public boolean intersects(Rectangle2D r) {
        return getBounds().intersects(r);
    }

It should probably be :

    public boolean intersects(Rectangle2D r) {
        if ( getBounds() != null ){
            return getBounds().intersects(r);
        }

    }

It should be probably be :

    public boolean intersects(Rectangle2D r) {
        if ( getBounds() != null ){
            return getBounds().intersects(r);
        }
        else{
            return false;
        }
    }

